+            // https://www.w3.org/TR/css-cascade-5/#at-layer
+            // Cascade layers aren't implemented, so `@layer <name-list>;` (which only
+            // declares layer order) is a no-op, and `@layer [<name>]? { <stylesheet> }`
+            // has its rules unwrapped in place rather than being discarded wholesale by
+            // the default case below. Without this, unlayered stylesheets emitted by
+            // Tailwind/PostCSS (which wrap effectively their entire output in @layer
